{
  "name": "Ley Lantern",
  "type": "equipment",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Ley Lanterns utilize stabilized and stored ley energy as a source to excite the normally dormant Arkna powder in the glass bulb. When excited in this way, the Arkna powder glows the same power and intensity of a torch, the benefit being that it is not actually an open flame, therefore being unaffected by environmental effects.</p><p>A normal Ley Lantern can burn for about 4 hours before expending its energy.</p><p>If a Ley Lantern is damaged while turned on, it explodes in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:5]{5 foot emanation} where it was damaged dealing @Damage[2d6[ley]]{2d6 ley damage} to all creatures within the emanation and the stored energy is expended.</p><p>If a Ley Lantern is turned off when it is damaged, the energy is not expended and does not explode.</p>"
    },
